ee, Northamptonshire, England":"Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England"},"nl":{"1465–":"1465–Overleden","1465–Female":"1465–Overleden","–1517":"–1517","1462–1522":"1462–1522","1490–1567":"1490–1567","1430–1490":"1430–1490","–Female":"Overleden","1567":"1567","1522":"1522","1465":"1465","1430":"1430","1462":"1462","1490 - 1495":"van 1490 to 1495","about 1485":"circa 1485","1490":"1490","1517":"1517","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England":"Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England"},"en":{"1465–":"1465–Deceased","1465–Female":"1465–Deceased","–1517":"–1517","1462–1522":"1462–1522","1490–1567":"1490–1567","1430–1490":"1430–1490","–Female":"Deceased","1567":"1567","1522":"1522","1465":"1465","1430":"1430","1462":"1462","1490 - 1495":"from 1490 to 1495","about 1485":"about 1485","1490":"1490","1517":"1517","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England":"Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Johanna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["feminine form of <i>Johannes</i> (  see  John  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Johannah","meanings":["feminine form of <i>Johannes</i> (  see  John  )."]},{"name":"Jonna","meanings":["contracted form of   Johanna ."]},{"name":"Jane","meanings":["Originally a feminine form of   John  , from the Old French form <i>Je(h)anne</i>. Since the 17th century it has proved the most popular of the feminine forms of <i>John</i>, ahead of   Joan   and   Jean .  It now also commonly occurs as the second element in combinations such as <i>Sarah-Jane</i>. In Britain it is still one of the most frequent of all girls' names. It is not a royal name, but was borne by the tragic  Lady Jane Grey  (  1537–54 ), who was unwillingly proclaimed queen in  1553 , deposed nine days later, and executed the following year. Seventy years earlier, the name had come into prominence as that of  Jane Shore , mistress of  King Edward IV  and subsequently of  Thomas Grey , 1st Marquess of Dorset, Lady Jane's grandfather. Jane Shore's tribulations in  1483  at the hands of  Richard III , Edward's brother and successor, became the subject of popular ballads and plays, which may well have increased the currency of the name in the 16th century. A 19th-century influence was its use as the name of the central character in  Charlotte Brontë's  novel Jane Eyre (  1847 ). From  1932 to 1959  it was used as the name of a cheerful and scantily clad beauty whose adventures were chronicled in a strip cartoon in the Daily Mirror. It is also borne by the American film stars  Jane Russell  (  1921–2011 ) and  Jane Fonda  (  b. 1937 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Johanna Cantelupe was born in 1465, in Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Henry Cantalupe and Joan. She married Oliver Wood about 1485, in Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in Somerset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1465–":"1465–Surnud","1465–Female":"1465–Surnud","–1517":"–1517","1462–1522":"1462–1522","1490–1567":"1490–1567","1430–1490":"1430–1490","–Female":"Surnud","1567":"1567","1522":"1522","1465":"1465","1430":"1430","1462":"1462","1490 - 1495":"1490 kuni 1495","about 1485":"umbes 1485","1490":"1490","1517":"1517","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England":"Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England"},"fi":{"1465–":"1465–Kuollut","1465–Female":"1465–Kuollut","–1517":"–1517","1462–1522":"1462–1522","1490–1567":"1490–1567","1430–1490":"1430–1490","–Female":"Kuollut","1567":"1567","1522":"1522","1465":"1465","1430":"1430","1462":"1462","1490 - 1495":"vuodesta 1490 vuoteen 1495","about 1485":"noin 1485","1490":"1490","1517":"1517","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Collingtree, Northamptonshire, Engla